{{Han compound|金|昔|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=metal}} – grindstone.

===Etymology===
; "whetstone, grindstone"
: From {{och-l|磋|to rub; to polish}} + suffix ''-k'' ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Related to {{och-l|厝}}.

; "criss-cross, interlocking, alternating, ornate"
: Related to {{och-l|醋}}, {{och-l|胙}} and {{och-l|祚}}. Perhaps semantically extended to "mistake" ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Though not noted by Schuessler, note phonetic and semantic similarities to {{cog|my|ဆက်|t=to join, connect}}.

; "lake"
: Borrowed from {{bor|zh|bo|མཚོ||lake}}.

; "cerium"
: Borrowed from {{bor|zh|en|cerium|'''ce'''rium}}.

